details.start_skating___club: She took up short track at age eight in The Hague, Netherlands. Hardrijvereniging Den Haag - Westland [HVHW]: Netherlands
details.hero__idol: Korean short track skater Choi Min-Jeong. (Athlete, 13 Nov 2018)
details.injuries: A concussion ruled her out of the 2019 World Cup events in Dresden, Germany, and Turin, Italy. (schaatsen.nl, 21 Jan 2019)
details.achievements: Finishing in second place in the overall competition at the 2018 Dutch Championships in Heerenveen, Netherlands. (schaatsen.nl, 09 May 2018)
details.other_information: RETIREMENTIn March 2020 she announced her retirement from competitive short track due to a heart defect. She had undergone heart surgery in 2014, having been born with supraventricular tachycardias. The condition would make her heart beat much faster than normal, and affected her training and development as an athlete. "Of course I would prefer to keep competing in short track, but it just doesn't work for me anymore. I am terribly disappointed because my Olympic dream has fallen apart." (ad.nl, 03 Mar 2020; Athlete, 13 Nov 2018; schaatsen.nl, 09 May 2018; dordtsport.nl, 29 Jan 2016)
details.superstitions__rituals__beliefs: She puts her right skate on before her left skate. (Athlete, 13 Nov 2018)
details.reason_for_choosing_this_sport: "My aunt went to the Olympic Winter Games in short track. My mother did it too, so it was obvious that I was going to do it as well."

details.start_skating___club: He took up the sport in 2016 in Leysin, Switzerland. Lausanne Short Track: Switzerland
details.hobbies: Cycling, listening to music, sport. (Athlete, 09 Feb 2023)
details.other_name: Pepito ["My first coach called me this, I don't really know the reason but I like it."] (Athlete, 09 Feb 2023)
details.awards_and_honours: In 2019 he took part in the torch relay ahead of the 2020 Winter Youth Olympic Games in Lausanne, Switzerland. (24heures.ch, 18 Nov 2019; Instagram profile, 02 Oct 2019)
details.sporting_philosophy: "Talent wins games, but teamwork and intelligence wins championships." [Michael Jordan] (Facebook profile, 29 Feb 2024)"Train hard, it will pay off." (Athlete, 09 Feb 2023)
details.hero__idol: Russian short track skater Victor An. (Athlete, 09 Feb 2023)
details.ambitions: To compete at the 2026 Olympic Winter Games in Milan-Cortina. He also plans to work as a coach or sports teacher once he retires from the sport. (Athlete, 09 Feb 2023; fisu.net, 03 Jan 2023)
details.achievements: Competing at the 2020 Winter Youth Olympic Games in Lausanne, Switzerland. (Athlete, 09 Feb 2023)
details.other_sports: He has competed on the speed skating World Cup circuit, and also participated in speed skating at the 2024 European Single Distances Championships in Heerenveen, Netherlands. (SportsDeskOnline, 12 Mar 2024)
details.reason_for_choosing_this_sport: He played ice hockey from an early age, and discovered short track through a recruitment programme that was looking for young sporting prospects ahead of the 2020 Winter Youth Olympic Games in Lausanne, Switzerland. "I received an email from my hockey coach. I went on to try the sport and I was hooked. The speed and contact with others is an incredible feeling. After more than eight years playing ice hockey, I was happy to move to an individual sport."
